body:
Hi React community,

I'm here to report a bug about the onselect event and its triggering use case. This is my first issue here, hope i've done it right.

Using this code :
```javascript
class App extends React.Component {
  render() {
    return(
      <React.Fragment>
        <input name={"testhtmlinput"}
                    onSelect={event => {
                        console.log("input onSelect is triggered");
                    }}
                />
      </React.Fragment>
    );
  }
}

ReactDOM.render(
  <App />, 
  document.getElementById('app')
);
```

Found behavior :
We observe onSelect event is triggered on focus, on click, on any text keydown and on left and right keydown.

React version and browsers :
This example has been written using a react 16.6.3 codepen. This issue has been found using react 16.4.2. I've seen this bug on firefox 60 and chromium 70.

Expected behavior :
onSelect event should be triggered only when one or more characters are selected within the input.

See this html and js example :
```javascript
<input name={"testhtmlinput"}
                    onselect="myFunction()"
                />

function myFunction() {
		console.log("input onSelect is triggered")
}
```

Here is what w3schools says about :

> 
> Definition and Usage
> 
> The onselect attribute fires after some text has been selected in an element.
[w3schools : HTML onselect Event Attribute](https://www.w3schools.com/tags/ev_onselect.asp)

What is the problem with this issue ? :
onSelect should be used for a specific behaviour but with your implementation it's fired in too many cases, then it's pretty much impossible to isolate the native behaviour and make it works fine.
